    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-10-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="247"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Captain Peslchouroff</persName> to <persName type="to"
                        >General Rousseau</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Archangel, Sitka</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="julian gregorian" when="1867-10-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 14–26, 1867.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">General</hi>: Referring to remark 2, at the foot of
                    inventory A, attached to the protocol of transfer, I beg leave to state, for the
                    information of the government of the United States, that the Russian American
                    Company value the chains, anchors, buoys, &amp;c., laid across the harbor at
                    this port, in the sum of $10,000 in gold.</p>
                <p>I am, general, your obedient, humble servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>A. PESTCHOUROFF.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>General <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovell</hi> H. R<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >ousseau</hi>, <hi rend="italic">United States Commissioner, &amp;c.,
                            &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
